description: Analysis of epidermal keratinocytes treated with TNFalpha in the presence of 10 uM parthenolide, an NF-kappa B inhibitor. Cells examined at various time points up to 48 hours following TNFalpha treatment. Results identify NF-kappa B-dependent subset of TNFalpha-regulated genes.

name: GDS1290

description: Analysis of CD4+ lymphocyte induced to differentiate into Th1 and Th2 by treatment with IL-12 and IL-4 respectively in the presence of TGFbeta. name: GDS1295
title: Lethal congenital contracture syndrome
description: Analysis of spinal cord from fetuses with lethal congenital contracture syndrome (LCCS). LCCS is autosomal recessive, causes death in 32nd gestational week, and involves degeneration of anterior horn motor neurons in spinal cord. Results provide insight into pathways active in motoneuron disease.

name: GDS1304
title: Cigarette smoking effect on small airway epithelium
description: Analysis of phenotypically normal 10th to 12th order small airway bronchial epithelia from cigarette smokers. Cigarette smoking is the most common cause of chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD). Results provide insight into the early pathogenesis of COPD.

name: GDS1310
title: Neonatal mononuclear cell response to lipopolysaccharide
description: Analysis of neonatal mononuclear cells from cord blood incubated with 5 ug/ml lipopolysaccharide (LPS). Effect of LPS on adult mononuclear cells from peripheral blood compared. Results provide insight into the molecular basis for increased susceptibility of neonates to sepsis.

name: GDS1312
title: Squamous lung cancer
description: Expression profiling of squamous lung cancer biopsy specimens and paired normal specimens from 5 patients. Differentially expressed genes integrated with protein interaction maps. Results suggest that differentially expressed genes are highly connected through protein interactions.

name: GDS1314
title: Malignant melanoma cell lines
description: Expression profiling of MelJUSO, A375, 607B, 518A2, and Skmel 28 malignant melanoma cell lines. Results correlated with regions of chromosomal breakpoints, and indicate an association between chromosomal breakpoints and altered gene expression.

name: GDS1317

description: Analysis of endothelial cells (HUVEC) isolated from umbilical veins subjected to high shear stress or high intraluminal pressure. name: GDS1329
title: Molecular apocrine breast tumors
description: Analysis of tumors of 49 breast cancer patients. Tumors classified into luminal and basal classes, and a novel molecular apocrine class. name: GDS1330

description: Analysis of platelets from patients with essential thrombocythemia (ET). ET is a myeloproliferative disorder resulting in an abnormal increase in the number of blood platelets. title: Glioblastoma pseudopalisading cells

name: GDS1381
title: Carboplatin sensitive and resistant ovarian carcinoma

description: Comparison of carboplatin sensitive and resistant ovarian cancer cells. Carboplatin is a chemotherapy drug. Cancer cells prepared from primary cultures of ovarian papillary serous adenocarcinomas. Results identify potential markers for carboplatin responsiveness in ovarian carcinoma.

name: GDS2444
title: Dichloroacetate effect on cultured lung carcinoma and glioblastoma cells
description: Analysis of A549 lung carcinoma and M059K glioblastoma cells treated with dichloroacetate (DCA), an inhibitor of the mitochondrial pyruvate dehydrogenase kinase. DCA shifts metabolism from glycolysis to glucose oxidation and decreases mitochondrial membrane potential in cancer cells.

name: GDS2444
title: Dichloroacetate effect on cultured lung carcinoma and glioblastoma cells
description: Analysis of A549 lung carcinoma and M059K glioblastoma cells treated with dichloroacetate (DCA), an inhibitor of the mitochondrial pyruvate dehydrogenase kinase. DCA shifts metabolism from glycolysis to glucose oxidation and decreases mitochondrial membrane potential in cancer cells.

name: GDS2445
title: Polycomb group protein depletion effect on embryonic fibroblasts
description: Analysis of embryonic fibroblasts depleted of the polycomb group (PcG) proteins EZH2, EED, SUZ12, or BMI-1. name: GDS2446

description: Analysis of HCT116 colon cancer cells in which tumor suppressor gene PTEN had been deleted by gene targeting. name: GDS2447
title: Transcriptional profiling of tobacco smokers versus controls
description: Analysis of lymphoblast cell lines derived from six subjects with active nicotine dependence. name: GDS2448

description: Analysis of CD34+ erythroid progenitors stimulated with erythropoietin (Epo) with or without LY294002, a PI3K inhibitor. name: GDS2452

description: Analysis of umbilical vein endothelial cells treated with 500 nM trichostatin A (TSA) for 24 hours. TSA is a histone deacetylase inhibitor. TSA treatment results in decreased endothelial nitric oxide synthase expression.

name: GDS2453

description: Analysis of histologically normal breast epithelia of breast cancer patients. Results provide insight into the molecular abnormalities in normal appearing breast epithelium in breast cancer and the roles these abnormalities play in carcinogenesis.

name: GDS3141
title: Colorectal mucosae from various regions of the large intestine
description: Analysis of colorectal mucosae from various regions of the normal large intestine. Results provide insight into the range of variation of gene expression in normal tissues.

name: GDS3144
title: Inflamed vascular epithelial cells response to apple extract enriched for procyanidins
description: Analysis of inflamed vascular endothelial cells treated with an apple extract enriched for procyanidins of low molecular weight. Results provide insight into possible protective effects induced by the plant derived procyanidins on the endothelial cells.

name: GDS3144
title: Inflamed vascular epithelial cells response to apple extract enriched for procyanidins
description: Analysis of inflamed vascular endothelial cells treated with an apple extract enriched for procyanidins of low molecular weight. Results provide insight into possible protective effects induced by the plant derived procyanidins on the endothelial cells.

name: GDS3147
title: GL7 determinant in various B-cell lines
description: Analysis of B-cell lines representing myeloma and Burkitt's lymphoma and exhibiting varied GL7 epitope expression. GL7high B-cells have higher functional activity for producing antibodies and presenting antigens. Results identify a candidate gene responsible for the biosynthesis of the GL7 epitope.

name: GDS3155
title: Dasatinib resistant and sensitive prostatic cancer cell lines
description: Analysis of 16 prostatic cancer cell lines treated with anti-tumor agent dasatinib. The cell lines display sensitivity or resistance to dasatinib.  Results used to define a gene expression profile associated with sensitivity to dasatinib.

description: Analysis of chondrocytes treated with a supernatant from SV40 T-antigen immortalized human synovial fibroblasts derived from a patient with rheumatoid arthritis (RA). Results provide insight into the molecular mechanism underlying RA-related cartilage destruction.

name: GDS3160
title: Methotrexate resistant colon cancer cell line
description: Analysis of HT29 derived colon cancer cells resistant to the anticancer drug methotrexate (MTX). Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms contributing to MTX resistance.

name: GDS3175
title: NF-kappaB and phosphotidylinositol 3-kinase inhibitor treated monocytes infected with the human cytomegalovirus
description: Analysis of monocytes treated with an NF-kappaB or a phosphatidylinositol 3-kinase (PI3K) inhibitor and then infected with the human cytomegalovirus (HCMV). Results provide insight into the role of NF-kappaB and PI3K in the activation of monocytes to a proinflammatory state after an HCMV infection.

name: GDS3177
title: Confluent and sub-confluent umbilical vein endothelial cell cultures
description: Analysis of umbilical vein endothelial cells grown to sub-confluency or confluency. Results provide insight into the molecular mechanisms underlying endothelial barrier formation.

name: GDS3179

description: Analysis of LM2 breast cancer cells depleted for metadherin (MTDH), a cell surface protein in breast tumors that mediates lung metastasis. description: Analysis of LM2 breast cancer cells depleted for metadherin (MTDH), a cell surface protein in breast tumors that mediates lung metastasis. name: GDS3309
title: Cigarette smoking effect on the nasal epithelium

name: GDS3313

name: GDS3315

name: GDS3318

name: GDS3325

name: GDS3609

name: GDS3626

name: GDS3627

name: GDS3628

description: Analysis of whole blood from rheumatoid arthritis patients at baseline of infliximab therapy. Infliximab is an anti-TNF alpha antibody. name: GDS3630

name: GDS4814
title: Ovarian cancer xenograft tumor response to trastuzumab and pertuzumab
description: Analysis of SKOV3 ovarian cancer xenograft tumors treated with trastuzumab (TZ), pertuzumab (PZ), or both. TZ and PZ target Human Epidermal Growth Factor Receptor 2 (HER2). name: GDS4818
title: Inflammatory breast cancer cell line response to TIG1 depletion
description: Analysis of SUM149 inflammatory breast cancer (IBC) cells depleted for TIG1. TIG1 depletion decreased IBC cell proliferation, migration, and invasion in vitro and inhibited tumor growth of IBC cells in vivo. Results provide insight into the role of TIG1 in the pathogenesis and progression of IBC.

name: GDS894

description: Analysis of effects of resistance exercise (RE) and time of day in skeletal muscle. Biopsies of male vastus lateralis muscle obtained 6 and 18 hours after acute RE, or no RE. Results suggest that RE may directly modulate circadian rhythms in skeletal muscle.

name: GDS968
title: Radiation therapy toxicity association with abnormal transcriptional response to DNA damage
description: Analysis of UV and IR irradiated lymphoblastoid cell lines derived from the peripheral blood of patients with acute radiation toxicity.  Samples taken 2 months after the completion of radiation therapy.  Results provide insight into the role of the response to DNA damage in radiation toxicity.

name: GDS969
title: Bone marrow prolonged storage effects
description: Analysis of impact of pre-analytical handling of bone marrow (BM). Time delays of 0, 24, or 48 hours between sample aspiration and RNA extraction examined. Storage of BM has dramatic effects on mRNA expression of individual transcripts.

name: GDS971
title: Rhabdomyosarcoma and Ewing's sarcoma comparison
description: Comparison of gene expression in 12 pediatric rhabdomyosarcomas (RMS) to that in 11 pediatric Ewing's sarcomas (EWS).   3 embryonic and 9 alveolar RMS tumors examined.  RMS and EWS appear similar in routine histology.  Results identify expression profiles that distinguish RMS from EWS.

name: GDS987
title: Kidney transplant response to calcineurin inhibitor-free immunosuppression using sirolimus
description: Analysis of kidneys from adult renal transplant recipients subjected to calcineurin inhibitor-free immunosuppression using sirolimus. Patients treated with sirolimus have a lower prevalence of chronic allograft nephropathy compared to those treated with cyclosporine, a calcineurin inhibitor.

name: GDS988
title: Kaposi's sarcoma-associated herpesvirus LANA overexpression in B lymphoid cells: time course
description: Expression profiling of B lymphoid cell lines overexpressing the latency-associated nuclear antigen (LANA) of Kaposi's sarcoma-associated herpesvirus. B cells made to express LANA from a tetracycline inducible promoter.  Expression examined at various time points up to 48 hours after induction.

name: GDS989
title: Kaposi's sarcoma-associated herpesvirus and Epstein-Barr virus infected cell lines
description: Expression profiling of cell lines BCBL-1 and BC-3 infected by Kaposi's sarcoma-associated herpesvirus (KSHV), Raji infected by the Epstein-Barr virus (EBV), and BC-1 infected by both viruses.  Results identify expression patterns specific to KSHV-infected primary effusion lymphoma derived cells.

name: GDS992
title: Endoplasmic reticulum membrane-associated genes in breast cancer cell line MCF-7
description: Identification of genes whose mRNA are translated from the endoplasmic reticulum (ER) in the breast cancer cell line MCF-7.  Secreted and membrane-bound proteins are preferentially translated in the ER.  Results provide insight into the association of membrane-bound proteins and breast cancer.

name: GDS999
title: Bronchoalveolar lavage cells of lung transplant recipients with acute rejection
description: Expression profiling of bronchoalveolar lavage cells of lung transplant recipients with acute rejection. Rejection status determined from biopsies. Results identify possible gene markers of lung transplant rejection.
